<div id="main_content">
	<h2>In Midst of Two Wars, UCF Expanding Focus on Global Peace and Security</h2>
	
	<p class="article_info">
		
			By UCF Staff
		
		<span class="date">Dec. 21, 2009</span></p>
	
	
	
		<div class="article_img" style="width: 345px;">

			<img alt="Article Main Picture" src="../resources/sites/UCF/content/live/NEWS/2000/NE2002/en_US/usipmain.jpg" height="226" width="345"  /> 
			
				<p class="photo_credit">Photo: Courtesy of U.S. Institute of Peace</p>
			
			<p>Jeffrey W. Helsing with USIP shakes hands with John Bersia (right), UCF's special assistant to the president for Global Perspectives.</p>
			
				<p class="note"><a class="full_photo" id="popup.jsp?article_id=002400417c223ec20125ae9931fd007eb9">Full Photo</a></p>
			
			
			
			
					
						
						
						
					
			
			
			
					
						
						
						
					
			
			
			
		</div>
	
	
	
	
	
	
	
		
